.TH EDIT 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
edit \- Edit published content.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
edit <path>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Identifies the published-content editing command name, but editing is unavailable in the current browser demo. No path is resolved and no editor or viewer is opened.
.SH FAILURES
Every invocation returns the stable command-rejected diagnostic:
.PP
Published-content editing is unavailable until authoring work is implemented.
.PP
The same outcome is returned for a missing, valid or extra path argument.
.SH NOTES
No virtual document, browser storage or pane state is modified. The public corpus is read-only; this manual does not promise an authoring workflow or compatibility surface.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ edit notes/sample-note.md
$ edit ~/about.md
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
open(1), less(1), login(1)
